### ğŸ”º Testing Pyramid

The classic testing approach with a solid foundation.

```
       â•±â•²
      â•±E2â•²        â† Few, slow, expensive
     â•±â”€â”€â”€â”€â•²
    â•± Int. â•²      â† Some, moderate speed
   â•±â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â•²
  â•±   Unit   â•²    â† Many, fast, cheap
 â•±â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â•²
```

**Distribution**:
- **70%** Unit Tests
- **20%** Integration Tests
- **10%** E2E Tests

**Benefits**:
- Fast feedback
- Easy to maintain
- Cost-effective
- Quick debugging

---

### ğŸ† Testing Trophy

Modern approach popularizing integration tests.

```
      ___
     /   \
    | E2E |        â† Few critical paths
    |_____|
   /       \
  | Integ.  |      â† Primary focus
  |_________|
 /           \
|   Unit      |    â† Support layer
|_____________|
   Static          â† Foundation
```

**Distribution**:
- **50%** Integration Tests (largest)
- **30%** Unit Tests
- **15%** E2E Tests
- **5%** Static Tests (foundation)

**Philosophy**: Integration tests give the best ROI

